ratings.comment: Julie is probably the best TA I have had thus far at this university. She is an incredibly fair grader who is genuinely interested in her subject material. Julie was always very calm and projected a happy face. She was willing to help me with something or explain it in more detail whenever I needed it. Overall, good discussion, good experience.

Not only did J.Keller maintain a comfortable class setting, but also provided and integrated compelling outside material with required lecture readings. Weekly sections often included a song/sound bite which sparked interest and enthusiasm to get discussion rolling. This of course helped our group utilize the 50 minutes most efficiently.
